# Repo Map

- Treat `claim + context + evidence` as the primary unit of truth.
- Canonical schemas live in `schemas/canonical/`.
- Typed extraction packet contracts live in `schemas/extraction/`.
- Human and agent dossiers live under `knowledge/`.
- Architecture decisions belong in `docs/adr/`.

# Operating Defaults

- Prefer derived rollups over hand-maintained summary booleans.
- Keep scoring explainable and versioned. Pipeline version constants live in `src/tool_db_backend/pipeline_versions.py`.
- If evidence is missing, leave a clear `TODO` instead of inventing a fact.
- Bump `EXTRACTION_VERSION` when prompts/schemas change; bump `MATERIALIZATION_VERSION` when derivation logic changes.
- Keep Markdown harness files up to date when behavior changes. Update the relevant agent, prompt, README, or design/spec `.md` files in the same change so instructions stay accurate.
- Mechanisms are biophysical (how molecular tools work); techniques are engineering methodologies (what category of method). See ADR 0002.
- Always parallelize I/O-bound calls (`ThreadPoolExecutor`). OpenAI API calls handle high concurrency (`llm_max_concurrency`). OpenAlex has a low RPM limit and needs a `Semaphore` gate on live calls only (`openalex_max_concurrency`).
